<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUN 94 / International Company News: Aros to quit bonds market-making
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Aros Fondkommission, the Swedish broker, plans to withdraw from
market-making in Swedish government bonds, Reuter reports from Stockholm.
It said it was withdrawing because of the difficulties of making a profit in
recent turbulent conditions. Aros, owned by engineering group Asea Brown
Boveri, is mainly involved in stockbroking, corporate finance and commercial
paper programmes.
In April and May the Aros made a positive result. It said it would continue
to make a market in state T-bills and related derivatives as well as
commercial paper.
