improved contribution' from CGIP's interests, which include a 32 per cent
stake in the CarnaudMetalBox packaging concern and 20 per cent of Cap Sogeti
Gemini, the computer services group.
CGIP should also benefit from the capital gains on disposals, including the
recent sale of control of Cedest to Holderbank, the Swiss cement group, for
FFr3.6bn. The group has been raising new capital to help pay for last year's
deal whereby it lifted its stake in CarnaudMetalBox.
