FT  07 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Beverley losses up to Pounds 2.67m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Beverley Group, the engineering concern, said yesterday that it had
completed its rationalisation programme and was now planning a placing and
open offer to fund future growth, both organically and by acquisition.
Details were expected to be announced shortly.
Rationalisation costs of Pounds 1.77m for the 1993 year pushed pre-tax
losses up from Pounds 276,000 to Pounds 2.67m.
Turnover of continuing operations fell from Pounds 12.84m to Pounds 7.97m.
