FT  07 JUN 94 / World Trade News: US and France in plastics venture
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DANIEL GREEN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Union Carbide of the US and Elf-Atochem of France, part of Elf Aquitaine,
are to create a joint venture to manufacture specialist plastics.
The move is the latest in a series of consolidations in the European
petrochemicals industry in response to low prices and competition from the
Middle East and Asia.
The venture will market polyethylene resins and compounds for the wire and
cable, pipe and other industries in Europe. It will take over Elf-Atochem's
the gas phase polyethylene reactor at Gonfreville, France, and Union Carbide
will license its Unipol process technology to the venture.
