FT  06 JUN 94 / World News in Brief: Massimo Troisi dies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Massimo Troisi, one of the most popular figures in Italian cinema, died of
heart failure, aged 41. He was renowned for the black humour of his work and
had just finished shooting Il Postino (The Postman), directed by Englishman
Michael Radford.
