<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JUN 94 / Arts (Openings): Van Gogh
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An exhibition of rarely-seen Van Gogh self-portraits goes on show at
Amsterdam's Van Gogh Museum on Friday. The 20 paintings and two drawings all
date from the artist's stay in Paris in 1886-7, when he was confronted for
the first time with the range of colours used by the Impressionists. Five of
the paintings have never been seen in public before. They were painted on
the backs of earlier works, and have been reframed so that both sides can be
viewed.
