<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JUN 94 / Business Travel: Bangladeshi strikes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Opposition parties may continue to call strikes at short notice in
Bangladesh and visitors may find travelling around the country even more
difficult than usual.
Strikes can suspend normal business throughout the country and make
travelling hazardous. People ignoring strikes can become targets for
violence and cars or buses may be damaged or destroyed.
There has been a marked increase in night - time armed banditry on main
roads between large towns in recent weeks and travel is not recommended
after dark.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>BDZ  Bangladesh, Asia.
</CN>
<XX>
